headline: Global Contract Logistics Growth Slows as Asia Leads and US Trade Policies Weigh
summary: DHL, GXO and other major 3PLs face cooling expansion in Europe and North America, while India emerges as a high-growth opportunity through 2029.

headline: Switch to UPS saved US Postal Service 43% in air transport costs
summary: The U.S. Postal Service is saving a great deal of money with UPS as its prime air cargo vendor instead of FedEx, according to a new inspector general’s report. The post Switch to UPS saved US Postal Service 43% in air transport costs appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: United Parcel Service (UPS): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, United Parcel Service’s shares (currently trading at $100.82) have posted a disappointing 18.6% loss, well below the S&P 500’s 5.7% gain. This might have investors contemplating their next move.
